---
source: crates/normalize/tests/cli_snapshots.rs
expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"rank\"])"
---
Rank code by metrics (complexity, size, coupling, duplicates, and more)

Usage: normalize rank [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version

Code quality:
  complexity       Run complexity analysis
  ceremony         Show ceremony ratio: fraction of callables that are trait/interface boilerplate
  uniqueness       Measure what fraction of functions have no structural near-twin per module
  call-complexity  Compute effective (reachable) cyclomatic complexity via call-graph BFS
  duplicates       Detect duplicate/similar code (functions or blocks)
  duplicate-types  Detect duplicate type definitions
  fragments        Find repeated AST fragments across the codebase

Module structure:
  size             Show hierarchical LOC breakdown (ncdu-style)
  density          Measure information density (compression ratio + token uniqueness) per module
  imports          Rank modules by import fan-in (requires facts index)
  surface          Per-module public symbol count, public ratio, and constraint score
  depth-map        Per-module dependency depth + ripple risk
  layering         Per-module import layering compliance — are imports flowing downward?
  module-health    Score each module across test ratio, uniqueness, and density (worst first)

Repository:
  files            Show longest files in codebase

Git history:
  hotspots         Churn × complexity hotspots: files ranked by change frequency and complexity
  coupling         Temporal coupling: file pairs that change together in git history
  ownership        Show per-file ownership concentration from git blame
  contributors     Analyze contributors across repos

Testing:
  test-ratio       Test/impl line ratio per module
  budget           Line budget breakdown by purpose (business logic, tests, docs, config, etc.)
